# Emotion Taxonomy for Oral Histories

## Belonging

Memories of home, community, kinship, village life, or rootedness.

## Loss

Memories connected to displacement, resettlement, death, disappearance, or rupture.

## Joy

Memories of festivals, food, play, weddings, laughter, friendship, and celebration.

## Care

Memories of cooking, caregiving, neighbourliness, women’s work, family labour, or mutual support.

## Longing

Memories of places, people, rituals, or ways of life that can no longer be fully returned to.

## Pride

Memories of skill, resilience, identity, survival, craft, knowledge, or community achievement.

## Reverence

Memories connected to prayer, sacred practices, elders, ancestors, burial, or spiritual life.

## Continuity

Memories showing how practices, recipes, values, or identities survive across generations.
